ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd recommend 751; it was a very nice overview of computational techniques applied to questions in biology. There is some programming entailed, so you should probably know at least some basic scripting.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The papers we read each week as part of the discussion section were very good, and the programming assignments provided nice grounds for practice in scripting. The early sections on alignment constitute material that every bioinformatician should know. Given how comprehensive the course really was, it was nice in that it enabled the student to know what is is out there.
